But nobody will know that because I said the same thing in the previous bullshit upload and it got deleted. So will this. So will your comment. Seems unfair to censor comments and prevent the torrent community from protecting itself from bullshit like this.

I don't really mind if someone uploads a program that can easily be downloaded from the original web site.

But it would be nice if they were up front enough to just say so, and include in the file description that its not a [k] file and you need to register to actually use the program (whether you have to pay or not), and not waste everyones time and band width, including our great host ThePirateBay!!

Just my opinion, for what its worth :-)
